PROSE PROSE PROSE
This change adds better documentation to describe the concepts behind how Normandy works, the mitigations we have in place to prevent compromise, and a specific, detailed example of how to go from nothing to an action being executed by the system add-on. It's intended for multiple audiences, but especailly for security and Firefox QA.
@mythmon r?
@casebenton r? I'd like your feedback as someone who is still very new to Normandy and would benefit from these kind of docs existing. Are we missing anything here that you don't understand? Do you find the docs useful?
@jvehent r? I'm probably missing a few things in the threat model section, so feedback on that in particular (and also on the entire document really) would be super-helpful.

